    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I think this should be an (optional?) subsection of the security considerations section. Privacy is a security consideration, and all non-obvious privacy considerations should be listed there.\r\n\r\nThere are plenty of EIPs where privacy considerations are not an issue. On the blockchain, everything is public by default, and everything should be assumed to be public except when commonly known to be private (e.g. private keys) or explicitly stated.",
